# Live Logs Handler

Thread-Safe Structured Logging SDK for Jupyter Notebooks. Captures all output from notebook cells (print statements, logging calls, errors) and writes them to structured log files in JSON or logfmt format.

## Features

- üßµ **Thread-safe logging** - Safe to use in multi-threaded notebook environments
- üìù **Structured output** - JSON or logfmt format for easy parsing and analysis
- üîç **Complete capture** - Captures logging.*, print(), and stderr automatically
- üì± **Cell context** - Tracks which cell generated each log entry
- ‚ö° **Non-blocking** - Background thread handles file I/O without blocking execution
- üéØ **Drop-in replacement** - Works with existing	 logging and print statements

## Installation

### Install from GitHub

You can install this package directly from GitHub using pip:

```bash
pip install git+https://github.com/yourusername/live-logs-handler.git
```

### Install a specific branch or tag

```bash
# Install from a specific branch
pip install git+https://github.com/yourusername/live-logs-handler.git@branch-name

# Install from a specific tag/release
pip install git+https://github.com/yourusername/live-logs-handler.git@v0.1.0
```

### Install in development mode

If you want to contribute or develop locally:

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/live-logs-handler.git
cd live-logs-handler

# Install in editable mode with development dependencies
pip install -e ".[dev]"
```
